<item>
            <title>[LU-2393] Test failure on test suite conf-sanity, subtest test_32b</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2393</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b7ec8778-35f1-11e2-8461-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/b7ec8778-35f1-11e2-8461-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_32b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;test_32b failed with 1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: conf-sanity 32b&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem has been seen more than once in SLES11 sp2 clients.&lt;br/&gt;
I believe this is a flawed test, but I can&apos;t spot the flaw.  Looking at the test log it appears that all the sums in the lists being compared really do match, but the sorted order of the lists are different.  Both lists are sorted right in the same test with similar command, so the order should come out the same.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have made several attempts to reproduce this failure manually, and haven&apos;t been able to do so.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
