                            <comment id="48423" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 13:24:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4685&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4685&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48420" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2012 12:46:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is due to the LC_COLLATE environment variable if set to &quot;C&quot; will sort differently than when set to &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; in precisely the way this bug is failing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
